<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">^</a></b> Blackwell, Christopher. <a href="http://www.stoa.org/projects/demos/home?greekEncoding=UnicodeC" class="external text" title="http://www.stoa.org/projects/demos/home?greekEncoding=UnicodeC" rel="nofollow">Demos: Classical Athenian Democracy</a>. 28 February 2003. The Stoa: a Consortium for Scholarly Publication in the Humanitiez. 25 April 2007.</li>
<li id="cite_note-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5" title="">^</a></b> Sprague, Rosamond Kent, <i>The Older Sophists</i>, Hacker Publishing Company (<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0872205568" class="internal">ISBN 0-87220-556-8</a>), p. 32</li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> Jarratt, Susan C. <i>Rereading the Sophists: Classical Rhetoric Refigured</i>. Carbon dale and Edwards ville: Southern Illinois University Press, 1991, p. 98</li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> Martin, Richard. "Seven Sages as Performers of Wisdom." <a href="/w/index.php?title=Cultural_Poetics_in_Archaic_Greece&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Cultural Poetics in Archaic Greece (page does not exist)">Cultural Poetics in Archaic Greece</a>. New York: Oxford, 1988. 108-130.</li>
</ol>
